\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 30. G. degenii} Bald. ex Degen,{\i  Österr. Bot. Zeitschr.}{\b  45}: 131 (1895) (incl.{\i  G. ossaeum} Halácsy). Forming a flat and lax cushion. Stems 5-20 cm, arising from a slender stock, 4-angled, densely hairy. Leaves 3-8 × 0·8-1 mm, in whorls of up to 6, linear to narrowly lanceolate, shortly awned, densely hairy; margin revolute. Inflorescence ovoid, compact, with few-flowered cymes, leafy; pedicels somewhat shorter to more than twice as long as flowers, divaricate. Corolla 3-4 mm in diameter, rotate, yellowish, hairy externally; lobes shortly apiculate. Fruit densely hairy. Limestone rock-crevices. •{\i  Mountains of Balkan peninsula, from S. Albania to E.C. Greece.} Al Gr Ju.
