\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 31. G. erythrorrhizon} Boiss. & Reuter, {\i Pugillus }51 (1852) ({\i G. debeauxii} Degen & Hervier). Caespitose; rhizome woody, branched. Stems 2·5-6 cm, ascending, slender, 4-angled, shortly hairy. Leaves 5-6 × 1-2 mm, in whorls of 4-6, widely to narrowly linear, acute, not awned, shining, coriaceous, sparsely and shortly hairy; margin more or less recurved. Inflorescence few-flowered, squarrose, leafy; pedicels 1-3 mm, deflexed after flowering. Corolla 2·5-3·5 mm in diameter, rotate, yellowish, glabrous; lobes shortly apiculate. Fruit shining, glabrous.{\i  Mountain rocks and screes. • S. Spain} ({\i Sierra Nevada, Sierra de Cazorla}). Hs.
