\pard\f0\fs28   Ser.{\i  Erecta} Pobed. Plants green or glaucous-pruinose. Stems 4-angled. Leaves usually less than 25 mm, but sometimes up to 40 mm, elliptical to filiform, the two surfaces more or less concolorous. Inflorescence narrowly oblong to ovoid, with lower branches short or long; partial inflorescences usually pyramidal; pedicels sometimes stout, often somewhat divaricate after anthesis. Corolla often white, or greenish, yellowish and reddish, rotate (or slightly cup-shaped), with usually apiculate lobes. The three groups of species ({\b 36-40}), ({\b 41-49}) and ({\b 51-58}) included in this Series are each very polymorphic polyploid complexes with different ecological and geographical centres; there are also several close connections among these groups.
