\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 33. G. litorale} Guss.,{\i  Fl. Sic. Prodr.}{\b  1}: 172 (1827). Stock strongly stoloniferous. Stems usually hairy above; middle inter nodes about as long as leaves. Leaves 10-18 × 2-5 mm, oblanceolate, abruptly narrowed towards apex, rather thick and shiny; margin slightly scabrid to smooth. Inflorescence narrowly ovoid, with short branches; pedicels stout, shorter than diameter of corolla, strongly divaricate. Corolla 3-4 mm in diameter, white, somewhat hairy outside; lobes shortly apiculate. Anthers dark when dry. Fruits 2-3 mm in diameter, globose, dark to blackish somewhat fleshy.{\i  Maritime sands. • W. Sicilia.} Si.
\par 

