\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 34. G. arenarium} Loisel.,{\i  Fl. Gall.} 85 (1806). Stock with very long subterranean stolons. Stems glabrous or rarely with long hairs, procumbent, with numerous non-flowering branches; internodes 5-10(-20) mm. Leaves 3-8 × 1-3 mm, broadly lanceolate, with short, hyaline apiculum, fleshy, shining; midrib slender; margin flat, slightly scabrid. Inflorescence few-flowered, long and narrow, with very short branches; pedicels 1-3 mm divaricate. Corolla 3-4 mm in diameter, yellow; lobes acute but not apiculate. Fruit c. 3 mm in diameter, globose, somewhat fleshy, rugose when dry. 2n = 66.{\i  Maritime sands. • W. France, just extending into N. Spain}. Ga Hs. 
